Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.38,0:00:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This jam is quite delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.68,0:00:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is homemade lingonberry jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.14,0:00:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness! Homemade?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.06,0:00:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was asked to show this photo\Nto the customers who enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.65,0:00:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the man who made this jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.78,0:00:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My, he made it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.74,0:00:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, his name is Conrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.16,0:00:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a place in the hills to the south\Nwhere lots of lingonberries can be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.29,0:00:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Over time, he eventually made\Nall the land there his.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.37,0:00:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess since he makes such good jams,\Nnobody complained, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.63,0:00:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he is a truly interesting man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.71,0:00:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He's also one of my few friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.26,0:00:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was his idea\Nto show this photo to customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.43,0:00:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants me to say, "Please come back\Nfor more Conrad Brand lingonberry jam."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll just have\Nto come back again for this jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.52,0:01:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we sure will.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.86,0:01:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll be glad\Nto hear you say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.47,0:02:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think\Nthis peaceful town will be attacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other methods than attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.94,0:03:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One town was wiped out with a single gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.31,0:03:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in 1958 in Zweifelstadt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.28,0:03:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There have been\Na string of murders in Lower Saxony.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.86,0:03:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The residents were so worried\Nthat their neighbor could be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.16,0:03:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a bloodthirsty killer that even\Nmundane events had people on edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.37,0:03:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The town was in a state of mass hysteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.08,0:03:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one of the residents\Nbought a gun for self-defense,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.17,0:03:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but ended up shooting a neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.13,0:03:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, they couldn't be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.88,0:03:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The town went up in flames
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and anything they could lay\Ntheir hands on became a weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.55,0:03:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole town killed one another\Nand there wasn't a single survivor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't think the same thing\Ncould happen here, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.73,0:03:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We must stop it before it begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.65,0:03:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.90,0:03:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably already begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.75,0:04:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me your money!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you've got some! Hand it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't take that money!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.42,0:04:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll just buy liquor\Nfor your alcoholic dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.80,0:04:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Too much liquor is bad\Nfor your health, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.72,0:04:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're helping him out, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.14,0:04:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get something to eat\Nat our usual place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.39,0:04:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,-Nice idea!\N-What do you guys want?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.44,0:04:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You must hate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.28,0:04:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You must hate them so much\Nyou want to kill them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.79,0:04:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk to Conrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.67,0:04:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a talk? About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.76,0:04:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,When we dropped by the cafe,\Ndidn't you notice how the owner, Ralph,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.26,0:05:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other customers smirked at us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.89,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That was just because\Nwe almost never go out as a couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Those people,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if they knew\Nwe won 20 million marks in the lottery,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.56,0:05:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows what they might do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.48,0:05:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.90,0:05:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I need to talk with him\Nbefore I lose my mind with paranoia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.66,0:05:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say that Conrad knows\Nthat I won 20 million marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.87,0:05:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What will we do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.21,0:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay him off\Nto make sure he keeps quiet about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.92,0:05:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if Conrad gets greedy\Nand keeps asking for more money?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.26,0:05:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.93,0:05:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.52,0:05:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the place where he gets\Nhis lingonberries around here somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.98,0:05:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.32,0:05:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.40,0:06:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Conrad's not such a bad guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.36,0:06:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.03,0:06:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not the kind of person\Nwho'd go and ruin
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.62,0:06:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the happiness we finally found, would he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.33,0:06:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.84,0:06:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.60,0:06:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey! Don't tell me you…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.27,0:06:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.52,0:06:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you do such a horrible thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.35,0:06:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,-I told you, it wasn't me!\N-Then who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.86,0:06:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I know!\NI haven't shot my gun since I bought it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.03,0:06:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up. That damn dog ticks me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.04,0:06:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It really pisses me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.96,0:07:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,-You sure are in a good mood today.\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.80,0:07:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did something good happen to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He finally came!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.18,0:07:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.02,0:07:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The wonderful guy\Nwho's going to take me away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.90,0:07:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink… Give me a drink…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.40,0:07:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.16,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in this town…\Nthey all laugh at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.79,0:07:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But it ain't damn funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.09,0:07:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.47,0:07:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't this…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.06,0:07:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.65,0:08:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Your son already took one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.41,0:08:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog stopped barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That was really interesting, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lipský.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.19,0:08:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the son of Franz Bonaparta,\Naren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.28,0:08:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me where your father is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.95,0:08:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in a race against time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.70,0:08:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless I hurry,\Nsomething terrible will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.49,0:08:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where your father is,\Ndon't you, Mr. Lipský?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The inspiration\Nfor that doll is Nina, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.80,0:09:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina's the one who told me\Nthat this is where you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.30,0:09:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina did?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.85,0:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.98,0:09:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.23,0:09:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have I been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.15,0:09:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.94,0:09:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You should continue\Nto rest for a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.78,0:09:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You stayed with me this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.70,0:09:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.04,0:09:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.46,0:09:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to die anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein\Nand Dieter will be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.38,0:09:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.05,0:09:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.64,0:09:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.68,0:09:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.31,0:10:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You were examining\Nall kinds of documents here, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.52,0:10:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.73,0:10:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine, so you can tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.03,0:10:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I got the former Prague secret police\Nand General Wolf's people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.91,0:10:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to get me all the information\Nthey could get their hands on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.75,0:10:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,About Franz Bonaparta?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.75,0:10:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. He's a very mysterious man,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.25,0:10:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm gradually getting\Na clearer picture of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.67,0:10:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a Czechoslovakian of German descent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently,\N"Franz Bonaparta" is also an alias.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.89,0:10:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After World War Two,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.43,0:10:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,many German-born Czechoslovakians\Nwere chased from their homeland, Bohemia,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.60,0:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but his family stayed in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When Czechoslovakia was\Nunder Communist rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.94,0:10:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not clear what kind of work\Nhe did for the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.11,0:10:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out he once married\Na Czech woman and they had a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.70,0:11:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, that child was a student\Nin the first book readings
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.29,0:11:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that he had already begun\Nin the mid-1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.55,0:11:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"Bonaparta has a son in Prague."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.59,0:11:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe these last words\Nof Petr Čapek were about this son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I also got my hands on
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a copy of an old photo of boys\Nin the book readings in the mid-1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.23,0:11:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the boy on the far left is--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.99,0:11:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a gifted child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.86,0:11:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.03,0:11:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he wasn't a gifted child,\Nhe was kicked out of the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.66,0:11:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Bonaparta didn't need him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.42,0:11:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe he's the man I met in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.50,0:11:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know where his father…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know where Bonaparta is?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.43,0:11:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.97,0:12:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is our only lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.47,0:12:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you hurry,\Nsomething terrible will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Something terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.77,0:12:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.44,0:12:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what Johan is trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.27,0:12:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What is he trying to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.11,0:12:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The perfect suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.53,0:12:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,True solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.61,0:12:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The only expression of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.49,0:12:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless we hurry,\Nmany innocent people will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Your bookshelf…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.00,0:12:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's full of picture books\Nthat Bonaparta wrote under pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.46,0:12:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've read almost all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.47,0:12:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,After reading many of them,\NI noticed something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.68,0:12:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oddly, all the characters\Nin his stories have German names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.27,0:12:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in this one, The God of Peace,\Nwritten under the alias Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But the issue with this one\Nis the pen name "Klaus Poppe."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.53,0:12:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The name "Franz Bonaparta"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.57,0:13:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and all his other\Npen names are Czech names.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.70,0:13:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But just this pen name is German.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.95,0:13:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be that Klaus Poppe\Nis the real name of your father,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.21,0:13:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,a Czech man of German descent?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.21,0:13:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A police detective who visited me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.38,0:13:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,arrived at the same conclusion\Nabout my father's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.76,0:13:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge of the BKA.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.35,0:13:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunge? He came here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.10,0:13:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but he left several weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.06,0:13:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He came to another conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.23,0:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, he doesn't really deduce things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.78,0:13:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He imagines\Nthat he is that person himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.36,0:13:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "I am Klaus Poppe."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.07,0:13:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"I have nowhere to go home to."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.58,0:13:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"To regain my peace of mind, I'll return\Nto the place dear to my heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.46,0:13:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Czechs of German descent were\Nchased out of Bohemia after the war
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.88,0:13:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and lost their homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.21,0:13:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where were his ancestors from in Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.17,0:14:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know exactly where.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do remember what my father\Nonce said when I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.51,0:14:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Our homeland was a town surrounded\Nby mountains in southern Germany."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.39,0:14:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I gave something to Inspector Lunge\Nthat I didn't want anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.27,0:14:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a postcard\NI was sent three or four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.74,0:14:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no return address.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.49,0:14:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a hand-drawn view\Nlooking down on a village
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.82,0:14:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that was signed "K.P."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.20,0:14:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"K.P."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.41,0:14:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.71,0:14:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all that I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.71,0:14:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Southern Germany…\NA town surrounded by mountains…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Will my father…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.71,0:14:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Will my father be killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.93,0:14:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But it certainly won't end there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.60,0:14:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.97,0:14:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Nina all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.18,0:14:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the play about this doll\Nto have a happy ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.94,0:14:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please protect Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.69,0:14:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.40,0:15:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what's about to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.74,0:15:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He's…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.24,0:15:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan's trying to recreate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.33,0:15:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The grisly tragedy at the Rose Mansion…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.04,0:15:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the massacre at Kinderheim 511.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.92,0:15:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.71,0:15:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens,\Ncome back alive, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.38,0:15:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.17,0:15:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I want you to live too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.02,0:15:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.14,0:15:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's begun to rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.62,0:15:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A drink…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.62,0:15:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a drink…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.20,0:15:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.84,0:16:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.80,0:16:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the police find Mr. Conrad's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No. He's still considered missing,\Nso they're investigating.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.84,0:16:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it! We never should have\Nhidden him in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.10,0:16:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If we'd told the police right away--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.43,0:16:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little late for that now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.10,0:16:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, even you believe I shot him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This never would've happened\Nif you hadn't won that lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.11,0:16:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you say that?\NYou're the one who bought those things!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.87,0:16:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no use waiting.\NThere are no trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.37,0:16:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,With all this rain,\Nthe bridges are flooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.12,0:16:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The roads are closed too\Nsince the river flooded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.09,0:16:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Isolated, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.30,0:16:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Things couldn't get any worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.88,0:16:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.84,0:16:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.22,0:16:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakob Vyrobek… and Emil Sebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.35,0:16:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,THE NAMELESS MONSTER\NMY GARDEN
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think Poppe and them are\Nall the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.48,0:17:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The drawings and subjects are\Ndifferent in each of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you're as much of an expert\Nas I am, you can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.11,0:17:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure why he used\Nso many different pen names though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.87,0:17:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The drawings are interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.75,0:17:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But I never did like\Nhis stories very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.33,0:17:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There are lots of picture books\Nwith dark themes in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.63,0:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But his aren't quite like those others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.76,0:17:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they different?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.72,0:17:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess you could say\Nthey're filled with malice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. There's one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.02,0:17:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a book by Helmuth Voss.\NIt was printed in 1989.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.07,0:17:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Only a few were printed,\Nso they're hard to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.45,0:17:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But to my eye,\Nthis author is also Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.95,0:17:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.50,0:18:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I said, once you're\Nan expert like me, you can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how much the style changes,\Ntheir peculiarities come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.09,0:18:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The story is different\Nthan those before it though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.84,0:18:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A thief escapes into a mountain village.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.22,0:18:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The thief plans on\Ncontinuing thieving in that village,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.02,0:18:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but as he interacts with the villagers,\Nhe forgets how to steal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.94,0:18:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he starts living a quiet life,\Nhelping the people of the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.48,0:18:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The title is The Peaceful House.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.49,0:18:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't leave me with\Nany of that bad aftertaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.99,0:18:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But now his drawings are no good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.74,0:18:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite odd, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.45,0:18:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,His stories got better,\Nbut he can't draw anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels as if he's lost\Nhis purpose or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.13,0:18:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Peaceful House…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.21,0:18:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A mountain village…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.72,0:18:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,"Our homeland was a town surrounded\Nby mountains in southern Germany."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.93,0:19:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,A map!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.18,0:19:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.10,0:19:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a map of southern Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.65,0:19:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.73,0:19:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A mountain village in southern Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.86,0:19:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,-Oh! Here it is!\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.16,0:19:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"Ruhenheim."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.66,0:19:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,RUHENHEIM\N(PEACEFUL HOUSE)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.87,0:19:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Good grief. This rain is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.13,0:19:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. How is it going?\NHave you found Conrad?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.17,0:19:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We can't find a trace at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.51,0:19:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My partners are still out searching now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I doubt they'll find anything\Nin this rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.68,0:19:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the river's flooded,\Ncutting off the railroad and roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.27,0:19:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As his friend, you must be worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.27,0:19:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth has happened\Nto this once tranquil town?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,First, Mr. Conrad goes missing,\Nthen Mrs. Hillman's dog was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.78,0:20:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Mrs. Hillman is bedridden\Nfrom distress now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.24,0:20:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Kemner was also beaten up\Nwhen he left the pub last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.96,0:20:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard he's in a serious condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.79,0:20:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We still don't know who beat him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.34,0:20:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If Mr. Kemner dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.63,0:20:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be the first murder\Nin the history of this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.22,0:20:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But even so, with all this rain,\NI can't get any backup.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.30,0:20:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I supposed to handle this\Nwith so few men?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.35,0:20:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's outsiders! Outsiders!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.60,0:20:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We never had any crime\Nin this town before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the work of outsiders!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.19,0:20:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're outsiders too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.82,0:20:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mean you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.82,0:20:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure is raining hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.91,0:20:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In this rain, I can't go outside\Nat all in this wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.54,0:20:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I'll get my partners\Nand have another look around town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.09,0:20:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.80,0:21:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, your shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.85,0:21:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they certainly are dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.23,0:21:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost as if\Nyou were walking around in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.69,0:21:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to use your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.92,0:21:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's that drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.29,0:21:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's not the type\Nwho would do anything so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.64,0:21:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? Are you out of gas?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.77,0:21:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or low on oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.94,0:21:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I can call you a repairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.37,0:22:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Another gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.54,0:22:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The lines must be down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.17,0:22:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't this be stopped?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.56,0:23:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitle translation by: Brian Athey
